      "repair_reason": "A maintainer explicitly paused automation for human review, and the remaining blocker is security-sensitive review/fix work on the PR branch rather than an unattended repair lane.; Needs attention: The patch introduces a concrete transcript-redaction coverage regression relative to current main's recursive full-message sanitizer.; Review finding: [P1] Preserve full content-block redaction coverage — src/agents/trans... (sha=d9accf89db1b0cce09b43e37bea76e430e6c1259)",
      "review_summary": "The PR replaces whole-message transcript redaction at `appendSessionTranscriptMessage` with a shared config-aware `redactTranscriptMessage` helper, threads `OpenClawConfig` through transcript write paths, adds redaction tests, and adds a changelog entry.\n\nReproducibility: yes. source-reproducible. A transcript message with a non-text content-block field containing a secret-shaped URL or token is redacted by current main's full-message `redactSecrets` path but would bypass the PR helper unless it is `text`, `thinking`, `partialJson`, or tool-call `arguments`/`input`.",
